text.__SUMMARY__: Rhinotyphlops ataeniatus is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae. The species is endemic to the Horn of Africa.
text.Geographic range: R. ataeniatus is found in eastern Ethiopia, northeastern Kenya, and Somalia.
text.Further reading: Boulenger GA (1912). "Missione per la Frontiera Italo-Etiopica sotto il commando del Capitano Carlo Citerni - Risultati zoologici - list of the Reptiles and Batrachians".
